article.headline: Auburn 64, Winthrop 62
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Korvotney Barber tipped in a basket with 2 seconds left, raising Auburn to a 64-62 victory over Winthrop on Thursday night. The teams, both 6-3, swapped leads seven times and Winthrop trailed again with 2:17 remaining before Torrell Martin's jumper tied the game, 60-60. Auburn's Quantez Robertson answered with a layup, that was matched by James Shuler tying the game once more at 62-62 before Barber's tip-in sealed the win. Auburn trailed 31-26 at halftime after Winthrop scored five unanswered points. The Tigers opened the second half on an 8-0 run, but Winthrop gained momentum -- leading by as many as 13 points early in the second half. Martin had a double-double with 19 points and a game-high 10 rebounds for Winthrop. Chris Gaynor added 17 points and Shuler had 14. Rasheem Barrett led Auburn with 19 points and Ronnie LeMelle added 12. Both teams hit seven 3-pointers. Auburn had 45.3 percent shooting, while Winthrop hit 42 percent of its shots. Winthrop outrebounded the Tigers 34-26, while Auburn forced 17 turnovers, scoring 15 points off them.
